4.Why are functions used in programming? Write two advantages.

-> Functions are used in programming to organize code into reusable, logical blocks that perform a specific task. They help make programs more structured, readable, and efficient.

 Two key advantages:

 1. Code Reusability
 A function can be written once and used multiple times in different parts of the program, 
 avoiding repetition and saving development time.

 2. Improved Readability & Maintainability
 Functions break complex programs into smaller, understandable parts, making the code easier to read, debug, and modify later.

